  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: cd8f8ce2fb929114f841c9e41beb59b6, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModuleContentController
  moduleImage: {fileID: 615001857}
  descriptionText: {fileID: 1649375052}
  moduleImages:
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 1814715926389068911, guid: de6b3856a1b72714c85fbd4fc9c538ca, type: 3}
  descriptions:
  - 'Computer Systems Servicing (CSS) is a technical-vocational field that focuses
    on the installation, configuration, maintenance, and repair of computer systems
    and networks. It includes both hardware (physical components like motherboard,
    RAM, hard drives) and software (operating systems, applications, and utilities).

    CSS
    is commonly offered in senior high school under the ICT strand and in technical
    training institutions. It prepares learners to become competent computer technicians
    who can handle real-world IT problems.'
  - 'The main purpose of CSS is to develop the technical skills and knowledge needed
    to work with computer systems effectively. Specifically, it aims to:

    - Train
    individuals in assembling and disassembling computer units.

    - Teach proper
    installation of operating systems and application software.

    - Develop troubleshooting
    skills for hardware and software issues.

    - Introduce basic networking concepts
    and setup.

    - Promote proper maintenance and safety procedures in handling
    equipment.

    Through CSS, students gain both theoretical knowledge and hands-on
    experience, which are essential in the IT industry.

'
  - "CSS is important in today\u2019s digital world because technology plays a vital
    role in almost every aspect of life. The need for CSS arises from the following:\r\n-
    High Dependence on Technology:\r\n > Schools, businesses, and government offices
    rely heavily on computers for daily operations.\r\n- Regular Maintenance Requirement:\r\n
    > Computer systems require proper maintenance to function efficiently and avoid
    system failure.\r\n- Troubleshooting and Repair Needs:\r\n > Technical issues
    such as system crashes, slow performance, and hardware failures require skilled
    technicians.\r\n- Growing IT Industry:\r\n > The demand for IT professionals
    continues to grow, and CSS provides entry-level skills for this field.\r\n- Cost
    Efficiency:\r\n > Instead of replacing faulty systems, organizations prefer repairing
    them, which requires CSS skills."
  - "CSS skills are widely used in various areas, including:\r\nComputer Assembly
    and Setup\r\n Building computer systems from components and preparing them for
    use.\r\nSoftware Installation and Configuration\r\n Installing operating systems
    (e.g., Windows, Linux) and configuring applications.\r\nTroubleshooting and Repair\r\n
    Diagnosing and fixing hardware and software problems.\r\nNetwork Setup and Maintenance\r\n
    Connecting computers through LAN, setting up routers, and ensuring network functionality.\r\nPreventive
    Maintenance\r\n Cleaning hardware, updating software, and ensuring systems run
    efficiently.\r\nTechnical Support Services\r\n Assisting users with computer-related
    concerns in offices, schools, or businesses."
  - 'National Certificate II (NC II) is a certification issued by the Technical Education
    and Skills Development Authority that proves an individual has achieved the required
    competency standards in a specific technical skill, such as Computer Systems
    Servicing.

    It is based on national competency standards and is awarded after
    passing an assessment conducted by TESDA-accredited assessors.

'
  - "The NC II certification serves several important purposes:\r\nValidation of
    Skills\r\n It confirms that a person has the necessary knowledge and skills in
    a specific field.\r\nStandardization of Competency\r\n Ensures that all certified
    individuals meet the same national standards.\r\nWorkforce Readiness\r\n Prepares
    individuals to be job-ready and capable of performing tasks efficiently.\r\nProfessional
    Recognition\r\n Provides formal recognition of a person\u2019s abilities in technical
    work."
  - "NC II is essential for both individuals and industries because:\r\nEmployment
    Requirement\r\n Many employers require NC II certification as proof of competency.\r\nGlobal
    Competitiveness\r\n It helps Filipino workers compete in international job markets.\r\nQuality
    Assurance\r\n Ensures that workers meet industry standards and perform quality
    work.\r\nCareer Opportunities\r\n Opens doors to better job positions, higher
    salaries, and career growth.\r\nConfidence and Credibility\r\n Certified individuals
    gain confidence in their skills and credibility in their profession."
  - "NC II certification is useful in many ways:\r\nJob Application\r\n Serves as
    a qualification when applying for technical jobs such as computer technician
    or IT support staff.\r\nPromotion and Career Growth\r\n Helps employees advance
    in their careers or move into higher positions.\r\nOverseas Employment\r\n Recognized
    as a valid credential for working abroad in technical fields.\r\nEntrepreneurship\r\n
    Enables individuals to start their own computer repair or IT service business.\r\nFurther
    Training and Certification\r\n Acts as a foundation for higher-level certifications
    (e.g., NC III, NC IV)."
